Welcome to the research study!  

 You are being invited to participate in a research study titled "Understanding opportunities for artificial intelligence (AI) -based natural dialogue systems in combating adolescent and young people's sexual, reproductive & health problems". This study
is being done by Audrey Nosenga from College of Business, Technology and Engineering at Sheffield
Hallam University. 
The project's objective is to assess the possibilities of sexual health chatbots for adolescents and young people. Medical chatbots that supplement clinical support for adolescents and young people by providing information on sexual, reproductive, and health issues are presumptively going to deliver accurate knowledge about sexual, reproductive health while leveraging self-efficacy and ensuring privacy.
For this study you will be presented with information relevant to "Understanding opportunities for artificial intelligence (AI)-based natural dialogue systems in combating adolescent and young people's sexual, reproductive & health problems". Then you will be asked to answer some questions about it. Your responses will be kept completely anonymous and confidential.
The study should take you around 2 minutes to complete. Your participation is entirely voluntary, and you can withdraw from the survey by closing your web browser and your data will be deleted from the study. You are free to omit any question. However,please note that after you have pressed the submit button at the end of the questionnaire you will no longer be able to able to withdraw from the study. 

By clicking the button below, you acknowledge:
